{"summary":"All four amendments have technical merit. Three address concrete correctness bugs in ambiguous run matching, duplicate run reporting, and journal-repair drift, while the remaining one usefully codifies a hidden parser invariant that is currently easy to violate silently.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-9-f0ca9b46","decision":"accept","rationale":"`CompletionJournalDetails::render()` and `completion_event_details()` currently encode the same ad hoc wire format in two places. The journal repair path parses service-emitted details and re-renders them through the fs-side formatter, so any future drift in field order or delimiters can turn an intended backfill into a duplicate append. Consolidating the formatter improves correctness and maintainability."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-1fa4f2f8","decision":"accept","rationale":"`CompletionJournalDetails::parse()` depends on `project_id`, `run_id`, and `plan_hash` never containing the literal `\", \"` delimiter, but that invariant is not obvious from the parser and is not fully enforced by the stored string types. Adding a comment or `debug_assert!` is a reasonable hardening step because it makes a real hidden assumption explicit before someone broadens those identifier shapes and silently breaks parsing."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-f4e1cccb","decision":"accept","rationale":"The current `update_task_run` fallback for a missing explicit `run_id` chooses a lone runless running row even when another running row for the same bead/project also exists. In the cited mixed `[run_id=None, running] + [run_id=run-2, running]` state, finalizing `run-3` rewrites one attempt while leaving another active, which is exactly the kind of ambiguous historical rewrite the port contract says to reject."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-6ff93073","decision":"accept","rationale":"`collapse_task_run_attempts()` only merges a start row into one matching terminal row; it does not remove repeated terminal rows for the same attempt. That means `find_runs_for_bead()` can overcount retries and outcomes when persisted NDJSON contains replayed duplicate completions, which is a real correctness issue for audit/reporting queries and should be normalized defensively."}]}